---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro'
---

<Layout
  title="Codex Prompt Master Agent | Terminal Workflow for Codex and Gemini | Pablo Suzarte"
  description="A portfolio page about Pablo Suzarte's terminal workflow for orchestrating Codex and Gemini with clear prompts, shared context, and human direction."
  lang="en"
>
  <header class="agent-nav">
    <div class="agent-nav__inner">
      <a href="/me-and-ai" class="agent-nav__back">&larr; Me and AI</a>
      <a href="/" class="agent-nav__logo">PS</a>
      <span class="agent-nav__title">Codex Prompt Master Agent</span>
    </div>
  </header>

  <main class="agent">
    <section class="hero">
      <div class="hero__glow hero__glow--a"></div>
      <div class="hero__glow hero__glow--b"></div>
      <div class="container hero__inner">
        <div class="hero__copy">
          <p class="eyebrow">Terminal orchestration</p>
          <h1>Codex Prompt Master Agent</h1>
          <p class="hero__lead">
            This is the operating model I use when I want Codex to build and Gemini to expand the
            thinking around the work. One project, one terminal, two AI strengths, one human
            direction.
          </p>
          <div class="hero__actions">
            <a href="#stack" class="btn btn--primary">See the prompt stack</a>
            <a href="#examples" class="btn btn--secondary">Open prompt examples</a>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="terminal-card">
          <div class="terminal-card__top">
            <span></span>
            <span></span>
            <span></span>
          </div>
          <pre class="terminal-card__code"><code>$ codex
Read the repo first.
Build the page.
Explain tradeoffs.
Verify with build.

$ gemini
Pressure-test the framing.
Sharpen the narrative.
Find better language.

$ human
Keep the vision coherent.
Choose what ships.</code></pre>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <div class="container">
        <span class="section__num">01</span>
        <h2>What this agent actually does</h2>
        <p class="section__lead">
          It is not a chatbot persona. It is a reusable prompt structure for running a serious
          collaboration loop in terminal. The goal is simple: keep the build lane fast, keep the
          thinking lane deep, and stop context from collapsing every time the conversation changes.
        </p>

        <div class="grid grid--3">
          <article class="card">
            <h3>Codex lane</h3>
            <p>
              Reads the codebase, makes changes, explains technical tradeoffs, and verifies the
              result against the actual project.
            </p>
          </article>
          <article class="card">
            <h3>Gemini lane</h3>
            <p>
              Pushes on framing, structure, research synthesis, and alternative directions when the
              work needs a wider lens.
            </p>
          </article>
          <article class="card">
            <h3>Human lane</h3>
            <p>
              Holds the brief, taste, priorities, and final decision. The human decides what the
              project is for and what must stay true.
            </p>
          </article>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="stack" class="section section--alt">
      <div class="container">
        <span class="section__num">02</span>
        <h2>The prompt stack</h2>
        <p class="section__lead">
          Good output starts before the task prompt. The stack below keeps both agents aligned on
          purpose, project state, constraints, and expected behaviour.
        </p>

        <div class="stack">
          <div class="stack__item">
            <div class="stack__index">1</div>
            <div>
              <h3>Role anchor</h3>
              <p>Define the job clearly: builder, reviewer, strategist, or editor. One agent, one primary responsibility.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="stack__item">
            <div class="stack__index">2</div>
            <div>
              <h3>Project context</h3>
              <p>State what the site is, who it serves, what already exists, and what should not be broken.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="stack__item">
            <div class="stack__index">3</div>
            <div>
              <h3>Task contract</h3>
              <p>Ask for a concrete outcome: add a page, rewrite a section, review a flow, generate alternatives, or tighten UX copy.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="stack__item">
            <div class="stack__index">4</div>
            <div>
              <h3>Constraints</h3>
              <p>Include tech stack, design rules, tone, file boundaries, validation requirements, and things the agent must avoid.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="stack__item">
            <div class="stack__index">5</div>
            <div>
              <h3>Response shape</h3>
              <p>Control the collaboration: findings first, edit directly, verify after change, keep explanations concise, show next steps.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="examples" class="section">
      <div class="container">
        <span class="section__num">03</span>
        <h2>Prompt examples I would actually use</h2>
        <p class="section__lead">
          The language matters. It needs enough direction to be useful, but not so much that the
          agent becomes stiff or ceremonial.
        </p>

        <div class="grid grid--2">
          <article class="prompt">
            <div class="prompt__label">Codex</div>
            <h3>Build prompt</h3>
            <pre><code>You are working inside my Astro portfolio.
Read the codebase first and preserve the existing visual language.

Task:
Create a new page for "Codex Prompt Master Agent".
It should explain how I use Codex and Gemini in terminal to build portfolio work.

Requirements:
- keep the current tone: direct, human, no corporate speak
- use the existing layout and design tokens
- add a discoverable link from /me-and-ai
- verify with npm run build

Do the edits, then summarize what changed and any risks.</code></pre>
          </article>

          <article class="prompt">
            <div class="prompt__label prompt__label--gemini">Gemini</div>
            <h3>Thinking prompt</h3>
            <pre><code>I am positioning a portfolio page called
"Codex Prompt Master Agent".

Help me strengthen the concept.
I want language for:
- what problem this solves
- why Codex and Gemini play different roles
- how a UX leader should talk about this without sounding like a solo hacker

Give me 3 framing options:
- sharp and strategic
- practical and teachable
- bold and future-facing</code></pre>
          </article>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section section--alt">
      <div class="container">
        <span class="section__num">04</span>
        <h2>The collaboration loop</h2>
        <div class="loop">
          <div class="loop__item">
            <strong>1. Frame the outcome</strong>
            <p>Describe what success looks like before asking for output.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="loop__item">
            <strong>2. Separate build from thinking</strong>
            <p>Use Codex for grounded repo work. Use Gemini to widen or challenge the idea.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="loop__item">
            <strong>3. Reconcile the two</strong>
            <p>Pull the strongest language or critique back into the build lane.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="loop__item">
            <strong>4. Ship only verified work</strong>
            <p>Every change should survive preview, build, and human review.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <div class="container outro">
        <span class="section__num">05</span>
        <h2>Why this matters in my portfolio</h2>
        <p class="section__lead">
          This is the bridge between UX leadership and AI-native making. I am not presenting myself
          as a lone engineer. I am showing that I can design the working conditions where ideas move
          faster, feedback gets sharper, and execution becomes more direct.
        </p>
        <div class="outro__actions">
          <a href="/me-and-ai" class="btn btn--primary">Back to Me and AI</a>
          <a href="/how-i-build-with-ai" class="btn btn--secondary">See the broader workflow</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

  <style>
    .agent-nav {
      position: fixed;
      top: 0;
      left: 0;
      right: 0;
      z-index: 100;
      backdrop-filter: blur(16px);
      -webkit-backdrop-filter: blur(16px);
      background: rgba(26, 22, 37, 0.82);
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
    }
    .agent-nav__inner {
      max-width: 1080px;
      margin: 0 auto;
      padding: 0.95rem 2rem;
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 1rem;
    }
    .agent-nav__back,
    .agent-nav__logo {
      text-decoration: none;
    }
    .agent-nav__back {
      color: var(--muted);
      font-size: 0.85rem;
      transition: color 0.2s;
    }
    .agent-nav__back:hover {
      color: var(--accent);
    }
    .agent-nav__logo {
      color: var(--text);
      font-weight: 800;
      letter-spacing: -0.04em;
    }
    .agent-nav__title {
      margin-left: auto;
      color: var(--muted);
      font-size: 0.78rem;
      font-weight: 700;
      letter-spacing: 0.08em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
    }

    .agent {
      padding-top: 4rem;
      background:
        radial-gradient(circle at top left, rgba(217, 119, 87, 0.14), transparent 32%),
        radial-gradient(circle at 85% 10%, rgba(91, 192, 235, 0.12), transparent 28%),
        var(--bg);
    }
    .container {
      max-width: 1080px;
      margin: 0 auto;
      padding: 0 2rem;
    }

    .hero {
      position: relative;
      overflow: hidden;
      padding: 5.5rem 0 3rem;
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
    }
    .hero__inner {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1.1fr) minmax(320px, 0.9fr);
      gap: 2rem;
      align-items: center;
      position: relative;
      z-index: 1;
    }
    .hero__glow {
      position: absolute;
      border-radius: 999px;
      filter: blur(80px);
      opacity: 0.4;
    }
    .hero__glow--a {
      width: 320px;
      height: 320px;
      top: 40px;
      left: -80px;
      background: rgba(217, 119, 87, 0.18);
    }
    .hero__glow--b {
      width: 260px;
      height: 260px;
      right: 4%;
      top: 90px;
      background: rgba(91, 192, 235, 0.16);
    }
    .eyebrow,
    .section__num,
    .prompt__label {
      font-size: 0.72rem;
      font-weight: 800;
      letter-spacing: 0.14em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: var(--accent);
    }
    h1,
    h2,
    h3,
    strong {
      color: var(--text);
    }
    h1 {
      font-size: clamp(3rem, 6vw, 5.4rem);
      line-height: 0.96;
      letter-spacing: -0.05em;
      margin: 0.85rem 0 1rem;
    }
    h2 {
      font-size: clamp(1.8rem, 3vw, 2.6rem);
      line-height: 1.05;
      letter-spacing: -0.03em;
      margin: 0.55rem 0 0.9rem;
    }
    h3 {
      font-size: 1rem;
      margin-bottom: 0.35rem;
    }
    p {
      color: var(--muted-light);
      line-height: 1.65;
    }
    .hero__lead,
    .section__lead {
      max-width: 720px;
      font-size: 1.05rem;
    }
    .hero__actions,
    .outro__actions {
      display: flex;
      gap: 0.85rem;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
      margin-top: 1.5rem;
    }
    .btn {
      display: inline-flex;
      align-items: center;
      justify-content: center;
      padding: 0.8rem 1.2rem;
      border-radius: 999px;
      text-decoration: none;
      font-weight: 700;
      font-size: 0.9rem;
      transition: transform 0.2s, opacity 0.2s, border-color 0.2s, background 0.2s;
    }
    .btn:hover {
      transform: translateY(-1px);
    }
    .btn--primary {
      background: var(--accent);
      color: var(--bg);
    }
    .btn--secondary {
      color: var(--text);
      border: 1px solid var(--border);
      background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.02);
    }
    .btn--secondary:hover {
      border-color: var(--accent);
      background: rgba(217, 119, 87, 0.06);
    }

    .terminal-card,
    .card,
    .prompt,
    .stack__item,
    .loop__item {
      background: linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.03), rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.01));
      border: 1px solid var(--border);
      box-shadow: var(--shadow);
    }
    .terminal-card {
      border-radius: 18px;
      overflow: hidden;
    }
    .terminal-card__top {
      display: flex;
      gap: 0.45rem;
      padding: 0.8rem 1rem;
      background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.03);
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
    }
    .terminal-card__top span {
      width: 0.7rem;
      height: 0.7rem;
      border-radius: 50%;
      background: rgba(232, 221, 211, 0.24);
    }
    .terminal-card__code,
    .prompt pre {
      margin: 0;
      overflow-x: auto;
      font-family: 'Courier New', monospace;
      color: var(--text);
      line-height: 1.65;
      font-size: 0.9rem;
      white-space: pre-wrap;
    }
    .terminal-card__code {
      padding: 1.3rem 1.4rem 1.5rem;
      min-height: 100%;
    }

    .section {
      padding: 4rem 0;
    }
    .section--alt {
      background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.025);
      border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
    }
    .grid {
      display: grid;
      gap: 1rem;
      margin-top: 2rem;
    }
    .grid--2 {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
    }
    .grid--3 {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(3, minmax(0, 1fr));
    }
    .card,
    .prompt {
      border-radius: 18px;
      padding: 1.25rem;
    }
    .card p,
    .prompt p {
      font-size: 0.92rem;
    }

    .stack {
      display: grid;
      gap: 0.9rem;
      margin-top: 2rem;
    }
    .stack__item {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 56px minmax(0, 1fr);
      gap: 1rem;
      align-items: start;
      padding: 1rem 1.15rem;
      border-radius: 16px;
    }
    .stack__index {
      width: 56px;
      height: 56px;
      border-radius: 14px;
      display: grid;
      place-items: center;
      background: rgba(217, 119, 87, 0.1);
      color: var(--accent);
      font-size: 1rem;
      font-weight: 800;
    }

    .prompt__label {
      display: inline-block;
      margin-bottom: 0.65rem;
    }
    .prompt__label--gemini {
      color: #7aa8ff;
    }
    .prompt pre {
      padding: 1rem;
      border-radius: 12px;
      background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.2);
      margin-top: 0.9rem;
    }

    .loop {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(4, minmax(0, 1fr));
      gap: 1rem;
      margin-top: 1.8rem;
    }
    .loop__item {
      border-radius: 18px;
      padding: 1.2rem;
    }
    .loop__item strong {
      display: block;
      margin-bottom: 0.45rem;
      font-size: 0.95rem;
    }
    .loop__item p {
      font-size: 0.88rem;
    }

    .outro {
      max-width: 760px;
    }

    @media (max-width: 900px) {
      .hero__inner,
      .grid--2,
      .grid--3,
      .loop {
        grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      }
    }
    @media (max-width: 640px) {
      .container,
      .agent-nav__inner {
        padding-left: 1.25rem;
        padding-right: 1.25rem;
      }
      .agent-nav__title {
        display: none;
      }
      .hero {
        padding-top: 5rem;
      }
      .stack__item {
        grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      }
      .stack__index {
        width: 48px;
        height: 48px;
      }
    }
  </style>
</Layout>
